{"questionId":"26972","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A transformation, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi></math>, of a plane is represented by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">r</mi><mo>′</mo><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">P</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">r</mi><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">q</mi></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">P</mi></math> is a <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mo>×</mo><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn></math> matrix, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">q</mi></math> is&nbsp;a <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mo>×</mo><mo> </mo><mn>1</mn></math> vector, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">r</mi></math> is the position vector of a point in the plane and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">r</mi><mo>′</mo></math>&nbsp;the position vector of its&nbsp;image under <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>The triangle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>OAB</mtext></math> has coordinates <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo></math>. Under T, these points are&nbsp;transformed to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo></math>,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;respectively.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">P</mi></math> can be written as <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">P</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">R</mi><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">S</mi></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">S</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">R</mi></math> are matrices.</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">S</mi></math> represents an enlargement with scale factor <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></math>, centre <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo></math>.</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">R</mi></math> represents a rotation about <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down the matrix <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">S</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"26972","referenceCode":"22M.2.AHL.TZ1.7b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write down the matrix S.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.9—Matrix transformations","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.14—Introduction to matrices"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}